{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd8881d4-c6db-4c7c-bbb5-a739e0ebb2b8","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. Since I can't inspect your specific workflow, here's a general guide for switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. NuGet.org setup\n- Go to **NuGet.org → Manage Packages → [your package] → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a **GitHub Actions** policy specifying your repo owner, repo name, and optionally the workflow/environment\n\n### 2. Workflow changes\n\n**Add OIDC permissions** to your job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace** the `dotnet nuget push` step:\n```yaml\n# BEFORE (API key)\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER (trusted publishing)\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_TOKEN: \"\"          # ensure no key is used\n```\n\nActually, the canonical approach is:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (OIDC)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget add source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --name nuget.org \\\n      --token-type oidc \\\n      --token ${{ steps.oidc.outputs.id-token }}\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\n> **Note:** As of mid-2026, NuGet trusted publishing support is still rolling out. Check the [NuGet blog](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/nuget/) and [GitHub docs on OIDC](https://docs.github.com/en/actions/security-for-github-actions/security-hardening-your-deployments/about-security-hardening-with-openid-connect) for the latest exact syntax.\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repo **Settings → Secrets** once verified\n- Consider using a GitHub **environment** (e.g., `production`) for additional protection with environment-scoped OIDC claims\n\n### Summary of changes\n| Area | Old | New |\n|------|-----|-----|\n| Auth | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC `id-token` permission |\n| NuGet.org | API key | Trusted publisher policy |\n| Workflow | `--api-key` flag | OIDC token exchange |\n\nWant me to look at a specific workflow file if you can point me to its path?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"989dae66-d69b-4f57-ad6a-453641bdf857","outputTokens":676,"requestId":"FE18:420A3:145FD99:16AF5F1:6A066E92"},"id":"78fc9bfe-8b24-4c34-a956-8e099ceb21a4","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:53.619Z","parentId":"83d41160-f031-48db-ae98-12b60426bfd0"}
